<ContentPage
  title="Cookie Statement — We Use No Cookies | LazyTools"
  description="LazyTools sets no cookies. No consent banner needed, because there's nothing to consent to. Here's exactly what that means."
  heading="Cookie Statement"
  updated="July 4, 2026"
>
  <p>
    <strong>LazyTools uses no cookies. None.</strong> That's why you don't see a cookie consent banner here —
    there's nothing to consent to.
  </p>

  <h2>What we use instead</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cookieless analytics.</strong> Page views are counted without cookies, fingerprinting or cross-site identifiers.</li>
    <li><strong>Local storage, locally.</strong> Some tools remember your preferences (like precision settings) in your browser's own storage. That data stays on your device, is never transmitted, and you can clear it anytime via your browser settings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If this ever changes</h2>
  <p>
    If we ever introduce anything that requires cookies (and we intend not to), this page will change first and a
    proper consent mechanism will appear before anything is set.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
